  "prompt": "I am already using Reliance Jio SIM card. How to check data usage on the same ?",
  "response": "Checking your data usage on a Reliance Jio SIM card is simple. Here are the methods you can use to check your data usage:\n\n### 1. **Using the MyJio App** (Most Recommended):\n   - Download and install the **MyJio app** from the Google Play Store or Apple App Store if you don\u2019t have it already.\n   - Open the app and log in using your Jio number.\n   - Once logged in, you\u2019ll see your data balance along with other details like voice call balance, SMS balance, and validity directly on the home screen.\n\n### 2. **Using the Jio Website:**\n   - Visit the official Jio website: **[https://www.jio.com](https://www.jio.com)**.\n   - Log in using your Jio number.\n   - Navigate to the \"My Account\" section to check your data usage and other details.\n\n### 3. **Using USSD Code:**\n   - Dial **\\*333#** from your Jio number.\n   - Follow the on-screen prompts to check your data usage.\n\n### 4. **Via SMS:**\n   - Send \u201c**BAL**\u201d to **199** from your Jio number.\n   - You will receive an SMS with your data balance, voice balance, SMS balance, and plan validity.\n\n### 5. **Using JioCare Customer Care:**\n   - Call **199** or **198** from your Jio number.\n   - Follow the IVR instructions to check your data usage.\n\n### 6. **Via JioChat App (Alternate Method):**\n   - Open the **JioChat app**.\n   - Log in with your Jio number.\n   - Go to the \u201c**Jio Services**\u201d section and check your data balance.\n\nThese methods are quick and easy to use, and the MyJio app is the most convenient option for regular monitoring of your data usage. Let me know if you need further assistance! \ud83d\ude0a",
  "temperature": 1.0,
